# Feature Branch Workflow

- Never commit directly to `main` or `master`
- Before starting any work, check the current branch with `git branch --show-current`
- If on `main` or `master`, create and switch to a feature branch first:
  `git checkout -b feature/<short-description>`
- Use kebab-case for branch names (e.g. `feature/user-auth`, `fix/login-redirect`)
- One branch per logical change or plan
